column5: I used to have one... Lost it when my computer crapped out last year.  Its Not a huge lake by any stretch of the imagination but I'd like to get another CPU file copy, before I start drawing from memory lol!
You can check http://www.anglersatlas.com/ . They have lots of free lake maps from the government.

Thanks, but no dice  Being a Dammed lake its levels fluctuate, so depths can be quite different month to month, and I'm guessing thats why I've never seen a proffesional topo map? There is a rendering out there but its not common...it lays out the old river path, and a few humps, even the old farm house. Its a decent little map... I'd love to have that Map back for a little trip pre planning/marking I'll keep looking, and cross my fingers.
Well...yes and no  Thats not the one I had....and the exsample pic is not Belwood lake. But they are selling a Map of Belwood lake, except its on back order LOL!
